{{Youmay|the [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] on [[Duro/Legends|Duro]]|[[Event Horizon (disambiguation)|other cantinas with the same name]]}}
The '''Event Horizon''' was a [[Cantina/Legends|cantina]] buried deep within the [[Rrudobar]] [[Space station/Legends|orbital]] [[City/Legends|city]] over the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Duro/Legends|Duro]], established by [[Clawfish]], a [[Quarren/Legends|Quarren]] criminal. It was well-known among [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]], gunrunners, and [[Outlaw tech/Legends|outlaw techs]] working the [[Corellian Trade Spine/Legends|Corellian Trade Spine]] as a source of illicit information or a good brawl.<ref name="CCW">''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]''</ref>

The cantina's most distinguishing feature was its dual-environment layout; half was reserved as a typical (if humid) cantina for terrestrial patrons, while the other half contained spas and wading pools for aquatic [[Species/Legends|species]]. The two halves were divided by the bar, which faced in both directions. There was a concealed escape tunnel leading to the street, which exited from the bar and a false crate in the storage area.<ref name="CCW" />

Placards on the walls warned [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidians]], [[Droid/Legends|droids]], and [[Skip tracer/Legends|repo agents]] to stay away.<ref name="CCW" />

